  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003cdiv data-alias=\"gutenberg-content__content\"\u003e\u003cp\u003eIt’s going to be a hell of a spring for Joel and Ellie, when \u003cem\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://tvline.com/t/the-last-of-us/\" id=\"auto-tag_the-last-of-us_1\" data-tag=\"the-last-of-us\"\u003eThe Last of Us\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/em\u003e returns for its second season in April.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eA new Season 2 trailer (above), which debuted Saturday during a SXSW panel featuring cast members \u003ca href=\"https://tvline.com/t/pedro-pascal/\" id=\"auto-tag_pedro-pascal_1\" data-tag=\"pedro-pascal\"\u003ePedro Pascal\u003c/a\u003e, Bella Ramsey, Kaitlyn Dever, Isabela Merced, Gabriel Luna, Young Mazino, Craig Mazin and Neil Druckmann, offers glimpses of both love and war. There’s Ellie (Ramsey) and Dina (\u003cem\u003e100 Things to Do Before High School\u003c/em\u003e’s Isabella Merced) sharing a slow dance, but there’s also stone-cold Abby (Season 2 addition Dever) marching through the snow, clearly on a mission.  The trailer closes with the suggestion of a betrayal by Joel (Pascal), as Ellie hisses at him, “You \u003cem\u003eswore\u003c/em\u003e.”\n\n\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv data-alias=\"cards__inner\" data-component=\"cards-related-content\" data-collapse-to-xs=\"false\" data-layout=\"inline\" data-size=\"md\" data-spacing=\"s-3\" data-cards-spacing=\"s0\"\u003e \u003cdiv data-alias=\"card__inner\" data-post-id=\"1235416007\" data-component=\"card\" data-has-background=\"false\" data-has-overlay=\"false\" data-layout-size=\"xs\" data-layout=\"sidebar\" data-main-alignment=\"s0\" data-main-spacing=\"s0\" data-media-position=\"\"\u003e\u003cfigure data-component=\"image\" data-alias=\"\" data-ratio=\"threeByTwo\" data-round=\"false\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://tvline.com/news/hacks-season-4-cast-julianne-nicholson-max-1235416007/\" title=\"\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"\" data-card-index=\"0\" data-post-id=\"1235416007\